Name: Description
Occupied Public Housing and Rent Regulat: Numbers and percents refer to the count and share of all occupied rental units for each geography. "Rent Regulated" includes any of the following building types: Rent-Stabilized pre- and post-1947, Rent-Controlled, HUD regulated (Section 8), Mitchell Lama rentals, and Article 4 or 5 buildings.

Name: Source Notes
Occupied Public Housing and Rent Regulat: U.S. Census Bureau, New York City Housing and Vacancy Survey (2002, 2005, 2008, 2011, 2014, & 2017); Retrieved from https://www1.nyc.gov/site/hpd/about/nychvs.page.
